articles.content: The Competition Commission of Singapore (CCS) has taken Courts and Prism+ to task over unfair practices. "Courts automatically added unsolicited items into consumers' shopping carts, while Prism+ used fake countdown timers and misleading stock indicators to pressure consumers into purchases," CCS added. Courts was found to have charged consumers for products they never selected
